The Last Testament, Vol 1
Interviews with the World Press
Talks given from 16/07/85 pm to 20/08/85 pm
English Discourse series
31 Chapters 

At the commune in America, for the first time ever Osho grants interviews to the world media. Included are questions from Good Morning America, Der Spiegel, 60 Minutes (Australia), The Guardian (England), Panorama (Italy), Portland TV, the Seattle Post Intelligencer and others. In dynamic, often humorous and always intimate exchanges, Osho talks with reporters about why he chose to break his years of silence, his views on the Pope, how the world can save itself from global suicide, and his own reputation as the "free sex guru",about criminal acts of Sheela (his secretary) and her gang in Commune.
Most of the 166 interviews Osho gave during the Ranch era and World Tour (see The Last Testament (Vol 1) to (Vol 6)) have never been published.
Here are 30 discourses (31st is unknown)
